Germany also would be prevented from producing or deploying chemmical or nuclear weapons. The United States wants a united Germany to be a member of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization and the Soviet Union has been staunchly opposed. The proposal was outlined by Soviet Foreign Minister Eduard Shevardnadze during international talks in East Berlin on the strategic future of a united Germany. The United States rejected the proposal, a US official said. The Soviet Union said today that a united Germany can join NATO after a five-year transition period during which all Soviet and US troops would leave the country. 